Typing Speed Game - p5.js

Description
This is a simple typing speed game built with p5.js. The game displays random single-digit numbers that the player must guess by typing the correct number on the keyboard. The game keeps track of the playerâ€™s performance, showing success or failure messages after each guess, and ends after a certain number of attempts or losses.

Features
A random number is displayed at the center of the screen.
The player must type the correct number to earn points.
The game keeps track of correct guesses, incorrect guesses, and total attempts.
After 3 incorrect guesses or 10 total attempts, the game ends and shows a game over message.
Players can restart the game by pressing ENTER.

How to Play
Start typing the number displayed on the screen.
If your input is correct, you get a success message.
If your input is incorrect, a failure message is shown.
After 3 losses or 10 total attempts, the game will show a "Game Over" message.
Press ENTER to restart the game.

Technologies Used
p5.js: A JavaScript library for creative coding.
HTML5: Used to structure the game and render it on the web.
JavaScript: For implementing the game logic and interactivity.
